<br>
Is there corruption in government?  Yes.  Is it always present?  I'm not so sure.  It's much easier to assume that someone's motives are bad simply because nobody likes to be fooled.  There are good people and bad people in all walks of life (not just polotics).<br>
<br>
If we are talking about something like the palistinian issue, it is natural for free societies to lean toward the Israeli side simplely because they are a free nations.  In palistine, you have teachings of hate, murder, repression of women and everything that I would assume a free nation would dislike.  Anyone can take a look at the Israelis and see what changes they need to make but it's a far cry from absolute distain for life and human rights the palistinians promote.<br>
<br>
I like to question my leaders, however I also like to tempor it with my own beliefs of right and wrong.<br>
