<br>
Of course, I do that too and I consider that every citizen's duty to do so. However, moral is such a subjective factor, that in the grand scheme of things, power of your military and power of your allies is what defines your borders. <br>
<br>
Since the last century, we try to let morale play a factor in international politics, but I think until now it has been a minor factor.<br>
<br>
Example : Many countries were opposed to the Iraq invasion, most of them shifted their standpoint when the invasion began.<br>
<br>
I am not dismissing the progress, though. Morale is what makes the US stay in Iraq and spent a huge deal of money on rebuilding the country. That is good to see.<br>
<br>
On free countries, it is easier to be 'nice' when you have a roof above your head and your belly is full. Palestinians never had a chance to build a country for their own, so it's not surprising there is less order amongst Palestinians. And I am not sure, but I think that the US is pretty much alone in their support for Israel. I think in most other countries people are not as unified in blaming one party for the conflict. Not sure on that, I never seen any numbers on it - I know it is the case in my own country. Anyway, I think if you take sides in this conflict, you are part of the problem, not the solution. <p>---------------<br>
The dorf formerly known as Merrahar...</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showMessageRange?topicID=195.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showMessageRange?topicID=195.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showMessageRange?topicID=195.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showMessageRange?topicID=195.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a> <b>5</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showPrevMessage?topicID=195.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showNextMessage?topicID=195.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=84><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.threadControl?topicID=195.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=195.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=195.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click